{
  "stem": "10588.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to continue the story, so when we went to work, what made it harder was that, first of all, it was, at that point, was not useful work.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because we could carry the same stone back and forth just to wear us out, to mock us, and to, to, you know, to have-- give them a chance-- their sadism to come up.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Secondly, if one fell or whatever, we couldn't-- we're not allowed to help each other openly.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We did it in, in hiding, but not openly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We could not speak on, on the-- so we had hardly any control.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For instance, like, we didn't have water to wash.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we used to go, just to feel the-- go through the motions sometimes in the morning.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I used to do that because I was used every morning to wash, you know, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And still would say, in the morning, the prayers, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And at night, even I had no longer my family to say it with me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But to try as much as I could, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So physically, I was totally enslaved.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I had no control of life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Spiritually, I could think and feel what I wanted.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I remember one time when I was in Auschwitz, and I felt the burden, the bitter taste of slavery.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I felt, if I would have a pencil and paper now, I would write a poem.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But there was no pencil and paper.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I told you, my earthly possessions were what I wore and the bowl, the enamel bowl from which we got the soup.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I wrote a poem in my, in my head.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I was liberated, when I came here to America, of course, I couldn't speak a word of English.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
